f(x) = x^4 - 6x^2
(0, 3)
4x^3 - 12x
(x_0, f(x_0))
4x_0^3 - 12x_0
y - f(x_0) = (4x_0^3 - 12x_0)(x - x_0)
y = (4x_0^3 - 12x_0)(x - x_0) + x_0^4 - 6x_0^2
x_0
(0, 3)
3 = (4x_0^3 - 12x_0)(0 - x_0) + x_0^4 - 6x_0^2
-3x_0^4 +6x_0^2 - 3 = 0
-3
x_0^4 - 2x_0^2 + 1 = 0 \implies (x_0^2 - 1)^2 = 0
x_0^2 = 1
